NAME
    gcloud alpha category-manager taxonomies describe - get the description of
        a taxonomy

SYNOPSIS
    gcloud alpha category-manager taxonomies describe TAXONOMY
        [GCLOUD_WIDE_FLAG ...]

DESCRIPTION
    (ALPHA) Get the description of a given taxonomy.

POSITIONAL ARGUMENTS
     Project taxonomy resource - The taxonomy to describe. This represents a
     Cloud resource. (NOTE) Some attributes are not given arguments in this
     group but can be set in other ways. To set the [project] attribute:
     provide the argument [taxonomy] on the command line with a fully specified
     name; provide the argument [--project] on the command line; set the
     property [core/project]. This must be specified.

       TAXONOMY
          ID of the project_taxonomy or fully qualified identifier for the
          project_taxonomy.

GCLOUD WIDE FLAGS
    These flags are available to all commands: --account, --configuration,
    --flags-file, --flatten, --format, --help, --log-http, --project, --quiet,
    --trace-token, --user-output-enabled, --verbosity. Run $ gcloud help for
    details.

API REFERENCE
    This command uses the categorymanager/v1alpha2 API. The full documentation
    for this API can be found at: https://cloud.google.com/

NOTES
    This command is an internal implementation detail and may change or
    disappear without notice. This command is currently in ALPHA and may change
    without notice. If this command fails with API permission errors despite
    specifying the right project, you will have to apply for early access and
    have your projects registered on the API whitelist to use it. To do so,
    contact Support at https://cloud.google.com/support/.

